## Steps to reproduce the issue

Consider the following piece of code:

module top  (y, clk, wire3, wire2);
  output wire [(32'h50):(32'h0)] y;
  input wire  clk;
  input wire signed [(5'h15):(1'h0)] wire3;
  input wire signed [(2'h3):(1'h0)] wire2;
  reg signed [(5'h15):(1'h0)] reg10 = (1'h0);
  assign y = {reg10};
  always
    @(posedge clk) reg10 <= (-$signed((-(wire2 << {wire3}))));
endmodule

Run with yosys version

   Generated by Yosys 0.9+4081,Yosys 0.15 (git sha1 UNKNOWN, clang 10.0.0-4ubuntu1 -fPIC -Os)

## Expected behavior
When passing the input wire2=4'h3,wire3=4'h3; I would expect the output to give 4'h8.


## Actual behavior
